  ('Stage 20','boss','Avoid triggering Frigid Vengeance with burst damage — use Poison or HP Burn to gradually reduce boss HP through thresholds.','Poison stacking','approved','human_observation','Poison damage bypasses Frigid Vengeance HP threshold triggers entirely — the boss HP drops through thresholds from DoT ticks without triggering the counterattack. Most reliable approach at stages 15-20 Normal.','fire-knight-ice-golem-seed-june-2026'),
  ('Stage 20','boss','Avoid triggering Frigid Vengeance with burst damage — use Poison or HP Burn to gradually reduce boss HP through thresholds.','HP Burn','approved','human_observation','Same bypass mechanic as Poison — HP Burn ticks do not trigger Frigid Vengeance. Can be combined with Poison for faster clears.','fire-knight-ice-golem-seed-june-2026'),
  ('Stage 20','boss','Keep minions dead or Block Revive active — alive minions during Frigid Vengeance make it ignore 100% DEF and near-certain Freeze.','Block Revive','approved','human_observation','Prevents minion revival entirely — Frigid Vengeance still triggers but revives nothing, so DEF-ignore remains minimal (50% per alive minion = 0% with none alive).','fire-knight-ice-golem-seed-june-2026'),
  ('Stage 20','boss','Resist or cleanse Numbing Chill — 50% Decrease ACC for 2 turns cuts debuff reliability in half.','Cleanse','approved','human_observation','Removes Numbing Chill immediately. Cleanser must act before debuff-landing champions to restore ACC before their turns.','fire-knight-ice-golem-seed-june-2026')
